## Sample matching

The most important practical step was sample matching. Metadata, microbiome, and metabolomics tables did not have identical sample coverage. The workflow therefore cleaned sample identifiers, checked overlap between omics layers, and retained only samples with matched metadata, microbiome, and metabolomics data.

The workflow started with `r fmt_num(metric_value("metadata_samples_total"))` metadata samples. Microbiome data were available for 1,638 samples and metabolomics data for 546 samples. After requiring paired microbiome and metabolomics data with usable metadata, 388 matched samples remained from 105 participants. To avoid repeated-measure leakage in supervised feature selection and final ranking, one matched stool sample per participant was retained for the primary independent analysis set, leaving 105 independent samples.

