The strongest nominal taxa results included Roseburia in UC vs non-IBD, Eubacterium in CD vs UC, Roseburia in CD vs UC, and Ruminococcus in IBD vs non-IBD. However, the lowest taxa q-values remained well above the FDR threshold. Therefore, these taxa were treated as exploratory signals only.

This is an important negative result. The project does not claim that individual genera are robust standalone biomarkers. Instead, the microbiome signal appears more consistent at the community level and in combination with metabolite features.

## Metabolite features showed stronger disease-associated signal

