The stronger metabolite signal suggests that stool metabolomics captured disease-associated molecular variation more directly than individual genus-level taxa in this matched subset.

## Feature selection for integration retained all filtered taxa and the strongest metabolite signals

Because no genus-level taxa survived FDR correction, all 39 filtered genus-level taxa were retained for integration. This was preferable to discarding the microbiome layer entirely, because community-level ordination and nominal taxa patterns still suggested diagnosis-associated structure.

For metabolomics, the integration set was restricted to the top 100 disease-associated metabolite features.

