## Taxa–metabolite correlations identified coordinated cross-omics signatures

Spearman correlation analysis identified 230 significant taxa–metabolite pairs after FDR correction. The strongest correlation was a negative association between Ruminococcus and C8p_QI7970 (rho = -0.490, FDR = 0.000452). Other strong pairs included Clostridium–C18n_QI4874, Eggerthella–C18n_QI4874, Coprobacillus–C18n_QI4874, Anaerotruncus–HILn_QI25565, and Ruminococcus–C8p_QI10300.

