# Conclusion

This project identified exploratory microbiome–metabolome candidate signatures associated with IBD disease state using a matched public HMP2/IBDMDB multi-omics cohort.

The final analysis retained 105 independent matched samples, tested 39 genus-level taxa and 40,306 metabolite features, identified 1,730 FDR-significant metabolite association results, found 230 significant taxa–metabolite correlation pairs, and ranked 230 candidate microbiome–metabolome pairs.

The strongest candidate was Ruminococcus–C8p_QI7970, an unannotated LC-MS metabolite feature pair supported by metabolite disease association, cross-omics correlation, and sPLS feature-selection evidence.

The results should be used as hypothesis-generating candidate signatures, not validated clinical biomarkers.

